annotation.TEXT: Oh, in fact... I should leave some coins behind for the moment, so I can go for the 3-star bonus. I'm just 2 coins away from 82, so let's try not to overshoot that mark.
Now, you will have to use that cannon to reach the blue gate switch, but first, you should use these dash arrows to blast a path through these chunks of cracked blocks.
Now, remember that gem at the very beginning?
Okay, fourth anger phase starts off the same way as the third anger phase.

Also, unlike when I landed in the brown cannon while it was changing between its preset angles before, you can't fire at an "in between" angle with a green cannon. If you try to, it'll still swivel to its next preset angle before firing.
...what are essentially barrel cannons from Donkey Kong Country!
Third normal phase strategy is just like in the second normal phase. It's just that he fires his higher shots at a faster rate, so definitely get down to the floor after his 2nd or 3rd low shot.
Yep, that's one way to do it. Alright, let's proceed to the last part of the level now.

Another thing of note, your mana and kill combos are preserved, and your mana will actually slowly regenerate (as if you were in midair without firing normally) while you're in a cannon, so that's pretty nice.

And, this can serve as a nice shortcut for Time Attack, if you do that and then carefully exit through the upper-right corner of this room. However, going that way skips a gem, so I'll want to exit the top center of the room instead.

Now for the final phase, his two barrels go in different directions, but you can find a decent opportunity to attack up close from the floor after his second low shot. Then back off and repeat as necessary.
My combo is still going! Oh, and here's a purple cannon. This one's neat. Enter it, and you have 3 seconds to adjust its angle with the mouse wheel before it fires.
I've still got a combo going. Let's see how far I can take it.
D'oh, I missed! But, fear not! If you miss it, you can always just try again. It's not like this is one of those gems that you get just one shot at.
Kablammo! You can just tear right through the shield bats in the way, although you don't get points for killing them that way.
...Yeah. That.
Whoa, I almost hit the green switch there again. If I did, I would've had to fly back up and hit a different switch again. Okay, now when you hit this "!" switch, you'll have 12 seconds to...
Okay, that wasn't exactly straight, but it was good enough.
There we go! Now, there's just one gem left, and it involves the red "!" switch, of course.

Now, remember how there was a vote for me to battle 3-BOSS (The King of Shooter) with Irvette? Yeah, that was actually a request from Keegster23, since he was using Irvette for that boss, and had struggled with it.
Third anger phase is basically two copies of the second anger phase.
There are a few cracked blocks that are just totally unreachable with either the cannon or the dash arrows. Also, I'm probably not going to break every single reachable block here.
Also, some cannons move or change direction periodically, so pay attention for those.
I also unlocked 6-9, and I believe I'll play that next.

Alright, that was the last enemy in the level. Now I just gotta find the last gem and clear the level. Hmm... Let's get all the coins here first. (There doesn't appear to be enough for me to reach 19 coins, unfortunately.)
So, I've gone over to my 100% file, and we're gonna play this level with Irvette here! (Oops, I forgot to pick a costume. Oh, well.)
Welp, I have no choice but to restart in that case. Wow, I can't believe I managed to get stuck like that, and that it was even possible for that to happen.
And now, to complete the level, just hit the green gate switch again, and that's basically it. Oh, and 3-star bonus FTW.
...Did that seriously just happen? (Oh, I should've put the "dood" soundbite here.)

This way, after hitting the blue gate switch, you can go through the path opened via the dash arrows below. If you didn't dash through those blocks first, you'd need to hit the yellow switch again and repeat the last few steps.

Now, remember the one-second delay here. Oh, and when you click on a green cannon, your firing angle is locked in right when you click, but if the cannon is moving, it'll still continue to move, so take that into consideration.
The 1 button will cause it to move out of there, after a few seconds. Try to time this right!
I can slip through there, right? ...Good. Okay, this run was a little sloppy, but...
Oh, and I can't move at all now!
Then, shoot yourself straight down the middle.
I used Taser Daria recently, so let's go straight to Panda Daria for this one.
Oh, and you can't squeeze in between a cannon and a wall this close to it, like here, as the cannon will suck you up anyway.
Really? I managed to line up perfectly with the harmful part of the spikes there? Well, whatever.
Flawless victory. (I'm not counting the dumb hit I took from the first regular enemy upstairs.)
Ack, I actually left that upper one in my way.
But, before I head over to it, I need to go back up here and hit either the yellow or blue gate switch so that the green gate next to the goal below closes.
Pfft... That was me being sloppy. It's okay. The remaining coins should heal almost all of that damage, so I'll enter the boss fight with practically full health.
And, I screwed up there. I needed to land in that upper brown cannon while it was pointing up.

Obviously, 12 seconds was way more than necessary. But, you need to have the green gate closed, or you'll dash straight into the goal without having any chance to go back and collect the gem.

C-C-C-C-COMBO BREAKER! (4 kills, 5000 points.)

I'm very low on mana, but I'm using Mira, so if I manage my mana carefully, I can still keep going with this combo!
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points.)

Hello, and welcome back to Miracle Fly! Here are the voting results this time: 1 vote for me to defeat The King of Shooter (3-BOSS) with Irvette, 1 vote for Tuxedo Mask Irvette, 1 vote for 6-B, and 4 votes for 6-8!
Let's see... Right about here... Yeah, I can't be hit here now, but I can sure hit him!

Okay, no getting myself jammed this time!

Now for the second phase, wait until he's fired two or three shots, then get down on the floor and blast him until he's about to launch more low shots, and repeat.

Green cannons won't fire until you click on them, while brown ones will fire automatically. They do give you enough force to tackle your way through cracked blocks, making getting the first gem here a piece of cake.
And then there'll be three more waves. Dodge the first wave by flying up, dodge the second by dropping down and getting close to him, and dodge the last one by hovering in the middle.
Monster combo! (10 kills, 27,500 points.)

Now, there is a gem buried in those cracked blocks down there, and the shards from those two bats would never be sufficient to reach it. But, I can just go up through these dash panels and then come back down.

...Or not, because I went through a one-way floor. So, I'll need to find some other way to get back down there and dash downwards through those blocks. (Yeah, you can't get that gem for a while.)
